.TH "tipc_recvmsg" 9 "tipc_recvmsg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tipc_recvmsg \- receive packet-oriented message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tipc_recvmsg
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *m "  ","
.BI "size_t buflen "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
network socket
.IP "m" 12
descriptor for message info
.IP "buflen" 12
length of user buffer area
.IP "flags" 12
receive flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used for SOCK_DGRAM, SOCK_RDM, and SOCK_SEQPACKET messages.
If the complete message doesn't fit in user area, truncate it.
.SH "RETURN"
size of returned message data, errno otherwise
